More popular style was deliberate outreach to a broader audience?
B.Zs.: We never plan to have a hit to boost CD sales.
That song is much more.
The album was designed to wrap the album, trying to lighten the orgy of tone and the harsher themes earlier in the CD.
How did you pick the six women singers?
Why did you pick the voices you did - what was your guiding principle?
B.Zs: The idea was to have a sound like a gospel choir.
